text: An election happened on November 3, 2020, to elect a Senator from the U.S. state of Virginia. The two candidates were Senator Mark Warner (Democratic Party) and Lieutenant colonel Daniel Gade (Republican Party). Mark Warner won the election and a third term in the Senate. There was a primary election for the Republican Party. There were three people in the Republican primary and Daniel Gade won. There was no Democratic Party primary because no one ran against Mark Warner. ==Democratic Party primary== Nobody in the Democratic Party went against Mark Warner in the primary, so no election happened. ==Republican Party primary== ==Results== ==References== Category:2020 United States Senate elections Category:Virginia elections
title: 2020 United States Senate election in Virginia
